        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-11-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-11-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="142" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d142">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Nelson</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 82.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-11-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">November</hi> 22, 1864</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                    despatches Nos. 152, 153, and 154, all under date of the 16th of October
                    last.</p>
                <p>Your correspondence with Mr. Covarrubias, transmitted with your No. 152,
                    returning thanks for the courtesies extended to you on the 4th of July last, is
                    deemed satisfactory and is approved.</p>
                <p rend="center">* * * * * *</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Thomas H. Nelson</hi>, Esq., &amp;<hi rend="italic">c</hi>., &amp;<hi rend="italic">c</hi>., &amp;<hi rend="italic">c</hi>.<hi rend="italic">, Chili.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
